annotation.TEXT: Seems like my orbit is slightly elliptical.
It's almost hypnotic... like a lava lamp...

Okay, so here are the voting results this time: 1 vote to try orbiting a magnet in zero-gravity (which I just did), 1 vote for Soldier Mira, 1 vote for Firefighter Irvette, 0 votes for 9-B, 1 vote for 7-7, and 4 votes for 7-5!
Well, there is something rather suspicious about this wall here...
I recommend resting to refill your mana before hitting this button. Alright, here we go!
Okay, now when you go around this way, DO NOT hit the first yellow gate switch. It is a trap, and hitting it WILL cause you to be pancaked against the blue gate block.
Yeah, it's best to blast that guy before trying to go up there.
Anyway, clearing 7-5 unlocked 7-6, but 7-7 got a vote, so I'll head there next with Cupid Daria. And, as the name suggests...

Actually, these are the only gravity switches in this level. However, they do force you to take on the red "!" challenge with sideways gravity. Combined with the darkness, that makes this one quite tricky.
If you said, "a gem", then you'd be right. Anyway, Mira does have a bit of an advantage here, being able to hit the rightmost blocks of that 3x3 square from over here.
Okay, I could hit the note button now, but I want to see if I can extend this combo further first.
Your best bet is to land on the ground to the right of the yellow switch, then slide to the left along the ground (or just let yourself be pushed by the moving wall, since it's not spiky here).
Blaster combo! (9 kills, 22,500 points)
Oh, what? How am I supposed to reach that gem? The 8 seconds from that timer switch below isn't nearly long enough!
Alright, that'll be all for this episode! To be continued... Ze! (...Wait, that's not right...) To be continued... OY! (No, that's still wrong!) To be continued... Yo! (There we go!)
To get the first gem, hit that yellow gate switch and get out of there before you get pancaked, then make your way back to where the gem is.
Alright, I have all the gems now, so let's make the gravity normal again to get the bookcase out of my way, and then get out of here.
So, let's start with 7-5, and bring along Soldier Mira, and try to figure out what "Presque Vu" even means. (UPDATE: SuperSupermario24 said what it means in the comments.)

Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! So, someone wanted to see if I could just orbit a magnet in a zero-g environment, so I'm back in 7-A (Barophobia) here to show this. Let me just get rid of these losers here first...
There we go. Now, let's do the Orbit Gum thing!
C-C-C-C-COMBO BREAKER!!! (6 kills, 10,500 points)

Whoa, nice. Usually, it's best to break the blocks to reveal the gem, but then wait until the next time the walls spread apart to grab it. (And now my OCD wants me to go back and break those last 3 blocks there.)
Okay, I've estabished my orbit, and now I'll continue circling around this magnet without doing anything.
Ha. Knew there was a guy up there.
However, enemies and spikes do not glow in the dark, so be very careful of those. Anyway, head to the left from here first.
For combo-hunters, there's a convenient pool of water here. Even Daria can get a good combo thanks to this.
The trickiest note is the one in the middle, and even that's not too bad.
Ha, sniped that one pre-emptively. Oh, and red buttons apparently glow in the dark as well. So, take a wild guess how the last two gems in this level are acquired.

Fun fact: One time, I got caught on the edge of the second yellow gate switch's ledge, and was squished by the left wall there, but I didn't die, and was instead pushed out of bounds somehow, which was silly.
Bah, I was hoping to include that guy in the combo I had going, but the combo probably broke while I was breaking those boxes next to the yellow switch for coins.
Yeah, unfortunately, there's a lot of waiting in this level.
Ooh, nice. The notes glow in the dark too, making it easier to see the hazards around here. Anyway, you get 15 seconds to grab all the notes, and it's not very difficult.
If I rushed there, maybe I could've rounded that bend in time, or maybe I just would've gotten myself shishkebabed.
ULTRA COMBO!!! (1 kill, 500 points!)
Wow, seriously... Quit flying like a drunk, Mira.
...Yeah, that was the only enemy in this level. Anyway, this level's main feature are these two moving walls with spikes on them.

Oh, hey! It's a hidden timer switch! And, this one gives you 14 seconds, which is should be more than enough time, even considering that you'll have to wait through one more wall cycle to reach the gem.
Now, if you look above, you'll see that the next safe spot is on top of a row of 4 cracked blocks. Try not to break them right away, for obvious reasons.
Pfft... How'd I managed to bang my head against the spiky ceiling there? (Too bad the helmet doesn't actually offer any protection.)
Awesome. So, there's just one more gem left to collect now, and it's clearly a red "!" challenge, so let's work our way over to that button.

Unfortunately, I couldn't complete the level from there, and when I tried to replicate that glitch later, I just died like normal. It would've been neat to show that glitch in this episode, but whatever.
Okay, now those blocks can be broken if you want. Anyway, let's circle around down here to the timer switch.
The walls don't close together completely, and instead leave 4 tiles worth of room between them, although it's more like 3-3½ tiles, due to the spikes.
Just make sure you don't get locked in this gem's room, for obvious reasons. Anyway, that's all of the gems, so I just have to finish the level now.
Oh, and guess what's hiding in the 3x3 square of cracked blocks to the left.
Okay, taking damage there didn't save me time. That hit was a screw up.
Don't mind me. I'm just taking damage to save time.
D'oh. I mistakenly thought there was a dude there... Well, I'll just let the combo end here then, rather than waste any more time. So, let's go back down for that note button.
LOL, there's that erroneous whistle again. Anyway, you get 24 seconds to wipe out a bunch of bats.
Whoa, I actually slipped perfectly between that guy and the spikes there.
Maybe it would've been faster to tank my way through that bat. Also, the health potion over there is totally not worth the time it would take to reach it.
Alright, that unlocked 7-8. So, your voting choices this time will be 7-6 (Rabbit Festival), 7-8 (Clockwise Library), and 9-B (Magma Tower).
...it's dark in here. But, not 100% dark. You can see a small area around your character, and certain things do provide a bit of light, such as your shots, and that gem over there.
Oh, and there's the exit, BTW.
For those that like coins, don't forget to open these boxes to the right of the yellow switch here.
Okay, with the first gem in hand, head up this way now.
And, don't rush forward too quickly, because you might crash into something that's hidden by the darkness. If you really want, fire shots ahead of you to scout for hidden duders.
Okay, not bad. Of course, I know I could've beaten 6600 if not for the unintended hit, and I'm sure 6700 and maybe even 6800 is possible.
Awesome! Just like that, I've full-comboed this level!

So, the main idea is to make progress while the walls are far apart, then get into the 3-3½ tile safe zone when they close together. Make sure you're not in a spot where you'll get crushed as they close together!
Okay, it was for Firefighter Irvette. Alright, here we go!
It gives you 8 seconds to get through the gate above, and it's best to hit the switch just as the walls start pulling away so you'll have the maximum amount of leeway.
Interestingly, the spikes lining the moving walls don't stretch all the way to the top of the level, so you actually do get the full 4 tiles of space to move around in up here.
Uh, oh. Looks like we've got some gravity switch shenanigans here. Remember those from older levels like Giddy Library?
Oh, turns out I could hit it from there with my laser. However, I imagine Irvette would have a difficult time hitting that one with her short-range shots without getting spiked.
Of course, do hit the second yellow gate switch to reveal the goal so you can finish!
Things get trickier here, as you've gotta tear through some cracked blocks quickly to advance.
Alright, I think we've seen just about enough of this. Now let's return to our regularly scheduled strawberries... I mean, adventure.

Most aren't that difficult to destroy, but the green one "under" the middle platform is really tricky to shoot without getting hit by the spikes (unless you're using Mira and her splash damage shots).
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Now, let's wrap up this episode by Time Attacking 3-6. Let me just pause the recording for a moment here while I double-check the Irvette costume vote...
